# Churn Prediction Model Suite
**Bell Canada · Technical Product Manager · 2022 – 2024**

---

## The problem

Bell was experiencing elevated customer attrition that was costing the business at a rate that had not been fully quantified. The existing approach to retention was reactive — agents attempted to save customers who had already called to cancel, with no predictive intelligence about who was at risk or what offer would actually retain them.

My analysis identified a **$6M annual profitability opportunity** tied to attrition that was preventable with the right intervention, at the right time, with the right offer, for the right customer.

The two models I shipped address fundamentally different moments in the customer journey. They are not variations of the same idea — they are two distinct intervention strategies requiring different architectures, different data pipelines, and different organizational workflows.

---

## Model 1: 1–30 Day Churn Propensity Model

### What it does

A batch propensity model that scores customers on their likelihood of churning within 1–30 days of a call interaction. The output feeds directly into outbound retention campaign logic.

### The intervention design

The model does not just predict — it drives a tiered offer engine. Customers are scored and segmented into probability brackets, and each bracket triggers a pre-defined, graduated offer:

- **High propensity bracket** → most lucrative offer (e.g. significant bill credit or device upgrade)
- **Mid propensity bracket** → mid-tier retention offer
- **Lower propensity bracket** → lighter touch outreach

Delivery is automated based on the segment: some customers receive a targeted SMS, others receive a different outbound communication. The offer is calibrated to the risk level — over-investing in low-risk customers wastes margin, under-investing in high-risk ones loses them.

### Why this matters

This model moved Bell from reactive retention (trying to save customers already calling to cancel) to proactive retention (reaching customers before they reach that point). The churn signal detected in the 1–30 day window gave the business enough lead time to act.

